WEBVTT

00:00:06.759 --> 00:00:09.621
Think back to a really vivid memory.

00:00:09.621 --> 00:00:10.617
Got it?

00:00:10.617 --> 00:00:14.955
Okay, now try to remember what 
you had for lunch three weeks ago.

00:00:14.955 --> 00:00:18.261
That second memory 
probably isn't as strong,

00:00:18.261 --> 00:00:19.928
but why not?

00:00:19.928 --> 00:00:23.207
Why do we remember some things,
and not others?

00:00:23.207 --> 00:00:26.549
And why do memories eventually fade?

00:00:26.549 --> 00:00:29.663
Let's look at how memories form
in the first place.

